Implemented Vercel Web Analytics for React as requested.

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics in the React School Management System project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed @vercel/analytics v1.6.1 using `npm install @vercel/analytics --legacy-peer-deps`
- Updated frontend/package.json with new dependency
- Updated frontend/package-lock.json with all transitive dependencies

### 2. Code Changes
**Modified: frontend/src/App.js**
- Added import: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react';`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the Router component (after opening Router tag)
- This placement ensures analytics tracking works throughout the entire application

## Verification
✅ Build completed successfully with no new errors
✅ Package.json updated correctly with @vercel/analytics dependency
✅ Package-lock.json updated with all transitive dependencies
✅ Existing code structure preserved
✅ All imports and exports remain intact
✅ No breaking changes introduced

## Technical Notes
- Used `--legacy-peer-deps` flag to resolve peer dependency conflicts with the existing react-scripts setup
- The Analytics component is placed inside Router to ensure it captures all routes and user interactions
- The implementation follows the Vercel Web Analytics documentation for React applications
- Plain React implementation used (as requested, not route-specific)

## Files Modified
1. frontend/package.json - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
2. frontend/package-lock.json - Updated with package and transitive dependencies
3. frontend/src/App.js - Added Analytics import and component

## Next Steps for Deployment
The analytics will automatically collect data once the application is deployed to Vercel. No additional configuration is required. The Analytics component will track:
- Page views
- Web vitals
- User interactions
- Custom events (if implemented)
